               <note type="summary">This document is a letter written by Governor
				John Sevier of Tennessee (1796-1801) to Cherokee Agent Silas Dinsmore, dated
				January 13, 1797. Sevier wrote the letter to inform Dinsmore that a man by the
				name of Abraham Martin reported that, while on his way to Cumberland, he lost a
				horse. Martin had reason to believe the horse was stolen by some Cherokees, and
				Sevier urged Dinsmore to inquire about the matter within the Cherokee nation
				and return the horse if possible.</note> 
			 
